<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFE4FFC5A5F8F8D61AB2F879" blockId="20.[136,1452,1374,2013]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFE4FFC5A5F8F8D61F19F8E9" bold="true" box="[189,294,1807,1833]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Notes:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFE4FFC5A463F8D61F96F8E8" authorityName="N. E. Brown ex Britton &amp; P. Wilson" authorityYear="1925" baseAuthorityName="Miller" box="[294,425,1806,1832]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Lippia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alba">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFE4FFC5A463F8D61F96F8E8" box="[294,425,1806,1832]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Lippia alba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a strongly aromatic subshrub characterized by the presence of hirsute branches; abaxial surface of the leaf blade tomentose; ovate bracts and pink, lilac or white corolla. It is a promising species in the pharmaceutical industry, one of the most used plants in popular medicine in 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFE4FFC5A6A0F88F1A13F8B0" box="[997,1068,1878,1904]" name="Brazil" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, being widely cultivated and used in the form of teas, compresses, baths, syrup, and extract (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFE4FFC5A662F8A21DC3F855" author="Santos, A. C. B. &amp; Nunes, T. S. &amp; Coutinho, T. S. &amp; Silva, M. A. P." box="[807,1020,1914,1941]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="980 - 991" refId="ref38734" refString="Santos, A. C. B., Nunes, T. S., Coutinho, T. S. &amp; Silva, M. A. P. (2015) Uso popular de especies medicinais da familia Verbenaceae no Brasil. Revista Brasileira de Plantas Medicinais 17: 980 - 991. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / 1983 - 084 X / 14 _ 083" type="journal article" year="2015">
Santos 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFE4FFC5A639F8A21D89F854" box="[892,950,1914,1940]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">et al.</emphasis>
2015
</bibRefCitation>
). It presents strong genetic variability regarding the chemical composition of the essential oils (chemotypes) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFE4FFC5A6E3F8461ABEF879" author="Tavares, I. B. &amp; Momente, V. G. &amp; Nascimento, I. R." box="[934,1153,1950,1977]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="204 - 220" refId="ref39466" refString="Tavares, I. B., Momente, V. G. &amp; Nascimento, I. R. (2011) Lippia alba: estudos quimicos, etnofarmacologicos e agronomicos. Revista Brazileira de Tecnologia Aplicada nas Ciencias Agrarias 4: 204 - 220. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 4400" type="journal article" year="2011">
Tavares 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFE4FFC5A143F8461A01F878" box="[1030,1086,1950,1976]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
